OL,3,CMan who stabbed sister in neck and set
OL,4,Con fire to be sentenced in January
OL,6,FQuoting from an interview given by the
OL,7,Fchild who was in the house, Mr Mallon
OL,8,Fsaid she heard an argument between her
OL,9,Fmother and uncle in Lithunanian, which
OL,10,Fshe didn't understand.
OL,12,FHe added that the child saw paramedics
OL,13,Ftreating her mother at the scene which
OL,14,Fis "an image she will take to the
OL,15,Fgrave."
OL,17,FMr Mallon added that Bracas "now
OL,18,Faccepts" his sister was "supporting
OL,19,Fhim" and that she was "not to blame
OL,20,Ffor anything."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/14
